WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:03.580 --> 00:00:07.010
How to Use Fresh Ginger Root.

00:00:07.010 --> 00:00:13.210
Enjoy the flavor and the health benefits of
fresh ginger root with a variety of preparations.

00:00:13.210 --> 00:00:23.430
You will need 3 1/2 oz. unsalted butter Fresh
ginger 7 oz. brown sugar 2 eggs 3 1/2 oz.

00:00:23.430 --> 00:00:31.760
self-rising flour Vanilla ice cream Honey
Olive oil Dried red chilies Cinnamon Cloves

00:00:31.760 --> 00:00:39.059
Bay leaves Onions Equipment: 4 1-c. ramekins
and garlic press.

00:00:39.059 --> 00:00:40.059
Step 1.

00:00:40.059 --> 00:00:45.610
Preheat the oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit
and melt the butter in a saucepan.

00:00:45.610 --> 00:00:49.970
Remove the melted butter from the heat and
add 1 tablespoon grated ginger and half of

00:00:49.970 --> 00:00:51.659
the brown sugar.

00:00:51.659 --> 00:00:55.019
Stir it up and add the eggs, stirring after
each egg.

00:00:55.019 --> 00:00:59.760
Then mix in the flour and divide the mixture
between 4 ramekins.

00:00:59.760 --> 00:01:02.949
Add an additional tablespoon of ginger for
extra kick.

00:01:02.949 --> 00:01:04.220
Step 2.

00:01:04.220 --> 00:01:08.770
Combine the remaining brown sugar with 1 cup
boiling water and pour it over the cake mixture

00:01:08.770 --> 00:01:09.930
in the ramekins.

00:01:09.930 --> 00:01:14.320
Loosely cover them with aluminum foil and
bake them for 25 minutes, and then remove

00:01:14.320 --> 00:01:18.710
the foil and bake them for an additional five
minutes.

00:01:18.710 --> 00:01:22.460
Serve the pudding hot with vanilla ice cream.

00:01:22.460 --> 00:01:24.050
Step 3.

00:01:24.050 --> 00:01:29.200
Thinly slice a 1-inch section of ginger, put
the slices in a cup, and pour boiling water

00:01:29.200 --> 00:01:31.350
over it to make ginger tea.

00:01:31.350 --> 00:01:34.980
Let the tea steep for a few minutes and serve
it with honey.

00:01:34.980 --> 00:01:36.230
Step 4.

00:01:36.230 --> 00:01:41.280
Finely grate fresh ginger root and add it
to olive oil, dried red chilies, cinnamon,

00:01:41.280 --> 00:01:46.590
cloves, bay leaves, and onions for a spicy,
tangy marinade.

00:01:46.590 --> 00:01:47.960
Step 5.

00:01:47.960 --> 00:01:51.840
Add a hint of ginger to your favorite recipes
that use cooking oil.

00:01:51.840 --> 00:01:55.810
Slice three or four 1/8-inch rounds of ginger
and whack them with the side of a knife to

00:01:55.810 --> 00:01:58.980
break up the fibers and release essential
oils.

00:01:58.980 --> 00:02:03.780
Add them to the heated oil, and fry them over
medium heat for about 30 seconds.

00:02:03.780 --> 00:02:08.050
Remove the ginger and use the infused oil
for your recipe.

00:02:08.050 --> 00:02:11.230
Ginger goes great with Asian recipes.

00:02:11.230 --> 00:02:12.560
Step 6.

00:02:12.560 --> 00:02:17.140
Peel and slice 1-inch sections of ginger,
put them in a garlic press, and squeeze the

00:02:17.140 --> 00:02:20.400
juice out for added flavor in any dish.

00:02:20.400 --> 00:02:21.590
Step 7.

00:02:21.590 --> 00:02:26.470
Include fresh ginger in your diet to relieve
discomfort caused by an upset stomach.

00:02:26.470 --> 00:02:29.190
Enjoy the varied uses of ginger.

00:02:29.190 --> 00:02:35.400
Did you know Detroit pharmacist James Vernor
created the first ginger ale in 1866 when

00:02:35.400 --> 00:02:40.060
he left his ginger-based concoction in an
oak keg for 4 years while he fought in the

00:02:40.060 --> 00:02:41.560
Civil War.

